ont color=#A0B0E0>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uslyydaugg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slyy Daugg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/20/01 6:54:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Get your Book of Souls - solo</span><hr size=1> Patience is a good virtue for a rogue, but when it comes to my Epic, I seem to lack it altogether.  I can't wait to get my grimy mits on the 'ol RB, and sitting around waiting for a Hate raid to invite me along so I can get my book wasn't working.<br>
<br>
I decided to take the plunge and devise a plan whereby I could just get up there and take it - with the encouraging knowledge that I would not be the first to accomplish this task.  Aye, it has been done before, and more than a few times I am guessing.  Now I am going to tell you how I did it, because I really believe I have found a great route to the book, and a good overall method for being prepared to steal the Book of Souls right out from under the noses of a packed house in Hate.<br>
<br>
First, if you are not strongly familiar with the outlay of hate, as I wasn't (having only been on two previous raids), study the main floor map, and the great explainations of it here:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.drawmjil.fakta.se/oc/guides/ipren2.htm">www.drawmjil.fakta.se/oc/...ipren2.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Second, get yourself a zone explorer here:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.everlore.com/LoreFiles/fileinfo.asp?ID=377137&sortby=4#Comments">www.everlore.com/LoreFile...4#Comments</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Study the map and use the zone explorer to familiarize yourself with the place, so you know like the back of your hand where the zone-in is, and where the nighstand where the book will be in-game is.  <br>
<br>
After some good study of each house on the main floor of hate<br>
and a review of the zone patrol that wanders between the houses and such, I believe I have worked out the safest route from zone-in house to nightstand:<br>
<br>
Immediately after zone in, hide/sneak and run out, take a right, and climb the east wall halfway up.  Do not go all the way up, or you may aggro a scorn or lich from above.  Along the east wall there are 8 houses, including the zone-in house.  Run just past the 4th house (including the zone-in house) , and take a left heading straight west.   When you see the fountain ahead you know you are doing well.  Run right over the fountain and keep heading straight untill you see the 2 clerics of Inny standing at the entrance to Maestro - go right past them into Maestro, hang an extreme right and go up the stairs.  Before you reach the top, though, be sure there is not a Scorn too close to the stairs, as she is one possible mob that can wander near the top.  When I went up she was spawned, but I saw that she had wandered very far from the stairs - so far in fact that the odds of her being close to the top I think will be very slim.  Now just run to the nightstand, grab your book, and gate out - done )  If you have used the zone explorer to practice this route, the travel from zone-in to gate-out should take less than 2 minutes.  I believe I was alone in Hate for all of a minute and a half.<br>
<br>
How to gate out cheap:<br>
Get a Leatherfoot Raider's Skullcap.  The hardest part is the alligator skin, but take it from someone who has owned 5 caps in his career (I always get one if I think I will need to gate out of someplace dangerous) the skin is best found on a bull alligator that spawns near the tower, but closer to the boathouse in Innothule ).  Get your shark skin in EFP far to right of the docks (merchant-bought ones won't work)  The Ring of Commons effect on it is INSTA-PORT -- no waiting around for the spell graphics, just BAM: LOADING, PLEASE WAIT.  And yes the cap is halfling only, but the effect will work for anyone.  A gate potion costs over 1kpp, which might not be much for some, but I don't spend a K on something if I don't have to.<br>
<br>
Don't forget - go naked, heh.  Guess I didn't have to say that, but oh well.  That goes for the porting Wiz too.  And the Wiz gates out immediately on zone-in, of course.  All you need to have when you go up is a sow and your Cap.<br>
<br>
I was scared to death when I went up, as you might guess.  What you might not guess is that what really had my heart pounding was the idea that I might fail after I put so much effort into casing the joint, charting a great path, and getting the fink outa there.  I was pumped to see my plan in action, and it went perfectly.  I'll bet my future Ragebringer it'll work for you too.  Ok that's pushing it, but you get my point P<br>
<br>
PS - thnx to Soldaris, 51 Wiz, who had the cahunas to port me up to a raidless hate, after a lvl 60 Wiz refused, calling me a nutcase.<br>
<br>
