<br>
FYI:  I had to keep logging in to Hate to check on book (about every 2 hours).  I camped up on the ramp right by Maestro's house.  I just made sure I was high enough to not agro the two wandering Liches that were pathing below but low enough to not agro anything on the second floor.  <br>
I logged in 3 times and each time I also proc'd the mask so I could see better.  Never got an agro.<br>
Then you just watch the Liches pathing below you and wait for a window in the pathing to jump off the ramp towards Maestro's house.<br>
<br>
Worked better than my first attempt when I would camp on the West wall.  Lich pathing is harder to avoid coming from that direction and, the third time I logged in, I ended up agro'ing another see invis mob that brought the whole damn area at me, lol.  Good thing lizard potion is instant.<br>
The only good thing about having done the West wall experiment first is that I learned more about Hate pathing in that area than I had known before and it was a rush be sneaking between houses with a full spawn around you.  <br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xandrax>Xandrax</A> at: 6/20/01 5:37:25 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uslyydaugg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slyy Daugg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/20/01 5:44:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Get your Book of Souls - solo</span><hr size=1> Well, anyway you want to gate out is fine.  Most rogues should already have the pottery skill to do it, I am guessing.<br>
