<br>
I think I will always prefer the cap anyway, though, because ending up in commons is a bit more convenient, usually - at least for me.  Also, the difficulty of attaining an aligator skin for the cap is terribly exaggerated - and that is the ONLY difficult part of the quest.  Most time I ever camped the skin was one hour, ever since I discovered that the bull aligator by the tower seems to have it about 1 in 6 or so spawns (once, I strolled in there an he had it first kill.)  In running through Innothule on the way to Guk, I have often heard lvl 20ish people begging for a skin in auction or in shout.  I always send them a tell, telling them where to hang out, and on more than one occasion I have gotten a tell back within and hour, saying, &quot;OMG thnx! I got my skin!&quot;  Whatever you do for this skin do NOT go running all around the swamp killing stuff trying to get bulls to spawn, it is a pointless endeavor.<br>
